# Frontend

This is the client-side of the Blog Ninja application. It provides a user interface for performing CRUD operations on blog posts.

## Tech Stack

The frontend is written in Next.js.

## Setup

To set up the frontend locally, follow these steps:

1. Navigate to the `front-end` directory.
2. Install the dependencies using `npm install`.
3. Start the application using `npm run dev`.

## Features

The frontend provides the following features:

- Viewing all blog posts.
- Creating a new blog post.
- Viewing a specific blog post.
- Updating a specific blog post.
- Deleting a specific blog post.
